00:00:30.730 --> 00:00:33.460
what is it/how it's made
Vinegar is a derivative of alcoholic beverages.

00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:37.420
To make their bottled delights, winemakers
ferment grapes with yeast.

00:00:37.420 --> 00:00:41.079
The yeast eat sugar from the grapes and poop
out alcohol!

00:00:41.079 --> 00:00:42.079
Yum!

00:00:42.079 --> 00:00:46.530
To make vinegar is the same, but acetobacter
bacteria is added to wine!

00:00:46.530 --> 00:00:50.870
The bacteria eats the alcohol and poops out
acetic acid.

00:00:50.870 --> 00:00:53.059
Acetic acid is what make vinegar, vinegar!

00:00:53.059 --> 00:00:58.770
The word vinegar comes from French for sour
wine, although it can be made from wine, beer,

00:00:58.770 --> 00:01:01.120
rice, or other fermentables like wood.

00:01:01.120 --> 00:01:05.580
Apple cider vinegar is made with -- you guessed
it, double fermented apple cider.

00:01:05.580 --> 00:01:08.250
Apples to hard cider to apple cider vinegar.

00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:10.360
Personal note: why did y'all mess up a good
thing?

00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:11.360
what's special about it?

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:16.180
According to the USDA apple cider vinegar
contains none of the vitamins A, B6, C, E,

00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:20.040
or K, and no niacin, riboflavin, thiamin,
pantothenic acid or folate.

00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:25.240
What it DOES contain, according to the FDA,
is a minimum of 4% acetic acid, and a lot

00:01:25.240 --> 00:01:26.240
of water.

00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:30.920
This means vinegar (or acetic acid) likely
won't make you thinner, and there's no scientific

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:32.890
support of it as a skin toner.

00:01:32.890 --> 00:01:37.090
And when Medscape General Medicine conducted
a review of the research on vinegar, they

00:01:37.090 --> 00:01:43.850
found it was not recommended as an anti-infectious
medicine orally or topically, and probably

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:45.900
doesn't fight hypertension.

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:50.490
And in terms of its cancer-fighting claims,
while it did shrink leukemia cells and tumors

00:01:50.490 --> 00:01:54.520
in lab experiments, but that affect hasn't
been shown in humans at all.

00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:55.520
